Gene.FullName: spindle and kinetochore associated complex subunit 3

SubmitterDescription.SubmitterName: International Standards For Cytogenomic Arrays Consortium (ISCA)

SampleDescription.Description: Interphase and metaphase FISH studies using probes within the duplicated intervals (RP11-47L4 and CTD-2318F22, respectively) confirmed these duplications and demonstrated that they are both located on a supernumerary marker chromosome. Therefore, a partial chromosome study was performed, which suggests that this marker chromosome is a derivative chromosome 13 from a 10;13 translocation that was likely inherited due to 3:1 meiotic segregation.

ClinicalAssertion.StudyDescription: Copy number variation identified through the course of routine clinical cytogenomic testing in postnatal populations, with clinical assertions as classified by the original submitter.
